{"title":"Emily Batty’s Signature Edition Canyon Lux Trail is a true Pro Model","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/08/20/emily-battys-signature-edition-canyon-lux-trail-is-a-true-pro-model/","date":1629470264000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Canyon just launched their newest bike, the Lux Trail ‘downcountry’ rig. With four different models to choose from, it’s the top end model that really stands out—though not just for the usual reasons. In an interesting twist, Canyon has devoted their top model as the EB-Edition. That EB of course stands for women’s MTB star, Emily Batty.</p><figure id=\"attachment_268890\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-268890\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20102319/Emily-Batty-Canyon-Lux-Trail-edition-facebook.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20102319/Emily-Batty-Canyon-Lux-Trail-edition-facebook.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x484/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" alt=\"Canyon EB-Edition Lux Trail\" width=\"1080\" height=\"1080\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20102319/Emily-Batty-Canyon-Lux-Trail-edition-facebook.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1080w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20102319/Emily-Batty-Canyon-Lux-Trail-edition-facebook-297x297.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20102319/Emily-Batty-Canyon-Lux-Trail-edition-facebook-800x800.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20102319/Emily-Batty-Canyon-Lux-Trail-edition-facebook-120x120.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20102319/Emily-Batty-Canyon-Lux-Trail-edition-facebook-768x768.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20102319/Emily-Batty-Canyon-Lux-Trail-edition-facebook-696x696.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20102319/Emily-Batty-Canyon-Lux-Trail-edition-facebook-1068x1068.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20102319/Emily-Batty-Canyon-Lux-Trail-edition-facebook-420x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 420w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20102319/Emily-Batty-Canyon-Lux-Trail-edition-facebook.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:484x484/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" ezoid=\"0.4275130256696724\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20102319/Emily-Batty-Canyon-Lux-Trail-edition-facebook.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1080w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20102319/Emily-Batty-Canyon-Lux-Trail-edition-facebook-297x297.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20102319/Emily-Batty-Canyon-Lux-Trail-edition-facebook-800x800.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20102319/Emily-Batty-Canyon-Lux-Trail-edition-facebook-120x120.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20102319/Emily-Batty-Canyon-Lux-Trail-edition-facebook-768x768.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20102319/Emily-Batty-Canyon-Lux-Trail-edition-facebook-696x696.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20102319/Emily-Batty-Canyon-Lux-Trail-edition-facebook-1068x1068.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20102319/Emily-Batty-Canyon-Lux-Trail-edition-facebook-420x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 420w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-268890\">Images c. <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/emily.batty.fanpage\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Emily Batty Facebook</a></figcaption></figure><p>Why is this a big deal? I’m struggling to think of a recent mountain bike launch where the top end model was the signature edition from a female racer. This isn’t just some pink-it-and-shrink it “women’s” bike. This is a true, top-level build kit with an eye catching paint job that will likely appeal to everyone—not just women.</p><p>In terms of geometry, this is exactly the same as the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/08/19/canyon-lux-trail-downcountry-bike-gets-new-front-triangle-slacker-geo-more-travel/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">other Lux Trail models</a> in the lineup.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20101606/Lux-Trail-EB-edition-Ergon.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20101606/Lux-Trail-EB-edition-Ergon.jpg\" alt=\"Ergon grips\" width=\"1230\" height=\"936\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20101606/Lux-Trail-EB-edition-Ergon.jpg 1230w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20101606/Lux-Trail-EB-edition-Ergon-297x226.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amaz