rail-EB-edition-Ergon-Shimano-XTR-1536x504.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20101552/Canyon-Lux-Trail-EB-edition-Ergon-Shimano-XTR-2048x672.jpg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20101552/Canyon-Lux-Trail-EB-edition-Ergon-Shimano-XTR-696x229.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20101552/Canyon-Lux-Trail-EB-edition-Ergon-Shimano-XTR-1068x351.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20101552/Canyon-Lux-Trail-EB-edition-Ergon-Shimano-XTR-1920x630.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20101552/Canyon-Lux-Trail-EB-edition-Ergon-Shimano-XTR-1279x420.jpg 1279w\"></a></p><p>What sets the EB-Edition apart other than the paint? The bike is built with a Shimano XTR 1×12 drivetrain and a Race Face NExt SL G5 Carbon crank. This build gets a Fox 34 StepCast fork with a DPS Factory rear shock, both remote lockout equipped. DT Swiss XRC 1200 Spline wheels are wrapped in Schwalbe tires with a 29 x 2.4″ Wicked Will up front and a 2.35″ Racing Ralph out back.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20101547/Canyon-Lux-Trail-EB-edition-colors.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20101547/Canyon-Lux-Trail-EB-edition-colors.jpg\" alt=\"Canyon Lux Trail Emily Batty color\" width=\"1230\" height=\"1230\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20101547/Canyon-Lux-Trail-EB-edition-colors.jpg 1230w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20101547/Canyon-Lux-Trail-EB-edition-colors-297x297.jpg 297w,https://biker