erumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20101547/Canyon-Lux-Trail-EB-edition-colors-696x696.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20101547/Canyon-Lux-Trail-EB-edition-colors-1068x1068.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/20101547/Canyon-Lux-Trail-EB-edition-colors-420x420.jpg 420w\"></a></p><p>And thanks to the consumer direct nature of Canyon’s business, you get this incredible build for a pretty reasonable $6,999—if you can find on in stock, of course.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.canyon.com/en-us/mountain-bikes/cross-country-bikes/lux/lux-trail/lux-trail-cf-9-eb-edition/3230.html?dwvar_3230_pv_rahmenfarbe=WH%2FBU#all-components-section-tab\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>canyon.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"753341701589ea351a70e35dba13ace707cf61a41159ce5f3b5bf7f6997e9a1e","category":"Cycling"}